- Why are you asking him that?
- He's not used to it yet.

161
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:33,664
他最好快一點習慣它
He better get used to it fast.

162
00:17:35,337 --> 00:17:36,665
我叫什麼？
What's my name?

163
00:17:38,632 --> 00:17:40,459
- 保羅
- 保羅什麼？
- Paul.
- Paul what?

164
00:17:41,302 --> 00:17:42,962
- 保羅·曼菲爾德。
- 拼出來。
- Paul Manfield.
- Spell it.

165
00:17:44,722 --> 00:17:47,391
M- A-N...
M- A-N...

166
00:17:48,602 --> 00:17:53,228
F- I-E-L-D.
F- I-E-L-D.

167
00:17:53,482 --> 00:17:54,762
- 你媽媽叫什麼？
- 別問了
- What's your mother's name?
- Just stop it.

168
00:17:54,858 --> 00:17:55,889
我等你說。
I'm waiting.

169
00:17:56,444 --> 00:17:57,523
辛西婭。
Cynthia.

170
00:17:57,612 --> 00:17:58,774
你弟弟呢？
And your brother?

171
00:17:59,363 --> 00:18:00,691
史蒂芬，行了吧？
Stephen, all right?

172
00:18:05,579 --> 00:18:07,370
你他媽的出什麼毛病了？
What the hell's your problem?

173
00:18:07,456 --> 00:18:09,283
我在市內找了些衣服。
I got some clothes in the city.

174
00:18:10,209 --> 00:18:13,874
你可以穿二手店的這些。新的這些衣服……
You can wear the thrift shop ones.The new ones...

175
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:16,040
要先洗一洗
have to be washed first.

176
00:18:16,799 --> 00:18:18,127
遵命，先生！
Yes, sir!

177
00:18:32,149 --> 00:18:33,976
今天下午，對不起
Sorry about this afternoon.

178
00:18:46,165 --> 00:18:47,493
我母親蘇菲去世了。
Sophie's dead.

179
00:18:51,170 --> 00:18:52,201
什麼？
What?

180
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:55,833
一個月前。癌症。
A month ago. The big "C."

181
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:02,129
哦，寶貝
Oh, babe.

182
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:08,142
聯邦調查局來之後，我告訴她我們沒事
I talked to her after the feds came,to tell her we were okay.

183
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:11,727
她從來沒洩露我們的消息。
She never let on.

184
00:19:14,321 --> 00:19:16,990
我都能看見她和莫裡斯站在那
I can just see her standing there with Morris.

185
00:19:17,324 --> 00:19:19,815
兩個胖胖的老猶太人，前布共產黨……
Two fat old Jews, ex-Bolsheviks...

186
00:19:19,994 --> 00:19:23,826
在洗衣房給他們紅尿布（指共產黨後代）的孩子打電話……
talking to their red-diaper baby on a phone from a Laundromat...

187
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,997
而她那時候已經快要去世……
and she's fucking dying.

188
00:19:30,881 --> 00:19:32,541
那女人很愛我。
That lady loved me.

189
00:19:34,384 --> 00:19:37,551
去年冬天，當他們安排我母親在芝加哥見我的時候
Last winter, when they arranged for her to meet me in Chicago...

190
00:19:37,888 --> 00:19:40,557
她在收到通知的一個小時之內就飛了過來
she flew there on an hour's notice...

191
00:19:40,975 --> 00:19:43,300
一個人，還下著暴風雪
alone, in a blizzard.

192
00:19:43,978 --> 00:19:45,805
她很害怕坐飛機的
She's terrified of flying.

193
00:19:46,314 --> 00:19:48,472
她下飛機的時候臉都綠了
She was green when she got off the plane.

194
00:19:49,151 --> 00:19:51,476
我帶她到休息室聊天
I took her over to the lounge to talk...

195
00:19:51,653 --> 00:19:55,982
我們坐在角落裡，我說「我希望事情容易一點」（I wish it was easier）
and we sat in a corner and I said,"I wish it was easier. "

196
00:19:56,826 --> 00:20:00,325
她說「應該說『我希望事情容易一點（You wish it were easier）』」
"You wish it were easier," she says.

197
00:20:01,664 --> 00:20:03,989
她竟然在糾正我的語法錯誤……
She's correcting my grammar...

198
00:20:04,334 --> 00:20:06,825
就像我是她教的小孩子一樣
like I'm one of the kids she teaches.

199
00:20:12,301 --> 00:20:14,626
現在已經沒有讓我們回去的動力了。
There's nothing left to go back to now.

200
00:20:15,847 --> 00:20:18,848
只有我們和孩子們了There's only us and the boys.

201
00:20:19,184 --> 00:20:20,844
只剩下我們了
We're all that's left.

202
00:20:22,229 --> 00:20:23,557
我們必須……
We must...

203
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:26,847
我們必須依靠彼此
We have to hang on to each other.

204
00:20:32,115 --> 00:20:33,573
我能看他的檔案嗎？
May I see his records?

205
00:20:33,658 --> 00:20:35,734
抱歉，我弄丟了
I'm afraid I lost his records.

206
00:20:35,827 --> 00:20:37,866
他們把檔案給我了，我也記得裝上了
They gave them to me,and I know I packed them...

207
00:20:37,954 --> 00:20:39,448
可是我就是找不到了
but I just can't find them.

208
00:20:40,082 --> 00:20:42,370
我一直丟東西，是不是？
I'm always losing things, right?

209
00:20:42,501 --> 00:20:45,502
我丈夫說，要不是擰上了，我連頭都能丟
My husband says I'd probably lose my head if it weren't screwed on.

210
00:20:45,963 --> 00:20:47,836
但是我可以重新做一份
But I can write for a copy.

211
00:20:47,924 --> 00:20:49,916
記得做一份檔案，好嗎？
Make sure to write for those records,okay?

212
00:20:50,343 --> 00:20:52,216
你可以選兩節選修課。
You can have two electives.

213
00:20:52,303 --> 00:20:55,423
音樂，打字，機械，電腦編程，還是家政？
Music, typing, mechanics, computer programming, or home economics?

214
00:20:55,515 --> 00:20:56,713
音樂。
Music.

215
00:20:58,518 --> 00:20:59,846
- 還有呢？
- 還有……
- And?
- And?

216
00:21:02,690 --> 00:21:05,359
- 家政吧。
- 他爸爸是廚師。
- Home economics.
- His dad's a cook.

217
00:21:23,671 --> 00:21:25,663
找個空座位，曼菲爾德先生。
Find an empty seat, Mr. Manfield.

218
00:21:27,008 --> 00:21:28,668
好的，聽著，各位
All right, listen up, everyone.

219
00:22:10,514 --> 00:22:12,174
再聽一遍。
Listen again, please.

220
00:22:52,519 --> 00:22:55,224
好的，現在有誰能告訴我這兩段音樂有什麼區別？
Now, can anyone tell me the difference between these two pieces?

221
00:22:56,023 --> 00:22:57,102
你說？
Yes?

222
00:22:57,190 --> 00:23:00,855
一個是流行，另一個是古典
One is pop and the other is classical.

223
00:23:02,697 --> 00:23:04,903
至少我知道你不是聾子
At least we know you're not deaf.

224
00:23:05,908 --> 00:23:07,865
你覺得呢，斯伯丁先生？
How about you, Mr. Spaulding?

225
00:23:08,411 --> 00:23:10,736
能不能給我們區分的更深一點？
Could you give us a deeper distinction?

226
00:23:11,665 --> 00:23:13,990
第一個很爛……
The first one's bad...

227
00:23:15,335 --> 00:23:16,877
第二個很好。
and the second one's good.

228
00:23:17,338 --> 00:23:20,208
這是個觀點，不是事實。
That's a matter of opinion, not a fact.

229
00:23:20,299 --> 00:23:23,466
這屋子裡一定有好幾個人不同意你的看法
I'm sure there are several people in this room who would disagree with you.

230
00:23:25,430 --> 00:23:27,588
你覺得呢，曼菲爾德先生？
How about you, Mr. Manfield?

231
00:23:27,807 --> 00:23:29,716
敢不敢試著說一下？
Would you care to venture a guess?

232
00:23:36,776 --> 00:23:38,400
你沒法跟著貝多芬的音樂跳舞
You can't dance to Beethoven.

233
00:23:43,616 --> 00:23:47,151
很好，曼菲爾德先生。你聽很多貝多芬的音樂？
That's very good, Manfield.Do you listen to much Beethoven?

234
00:23:48,372 --> 00:23:49,617
不，沒有。
No, not really.

235
00:23:49,706 --> 00:23:51,698
那你怎麼聽出這段是貝多芬？
How did you identify this piece?

236
00:23:53,711 --> 00:23:54,873
我猜我之前聽過這段吧。
I guess I've heard some.

237
00:23:56,214 --> 00:23:59,168
我確定班裡的其他人也能聽出另一個作者
I'm sure the rest of the class can identify the other composer.

238
00:24:01,094 --> 00:24:03,382
說的很對。沒法跟著貝多芬的音樂跳舞。
You're quite correct.abcYou can't dance to Mr. Beethoven.

239
00:24:03,597 --> 00:24:05,839
能告訴我為什麼嗎，曼菲爾德先生？
Can you tell me why, Mr. Manfield?

240
00:24:07,559 --> 00:24:09,801
因為貝多芬的這段……
Because the Beethoven piece...

241
00:24:09,895 --> 00:24:14,142
沒有一個固定的節奏，或者說拍子
doesn't use a constant rhythm or tempo!

242
00:24:18,655 --> 00:24:21,110
麥當娜的歌一直都是四四拍
Madonna is 4/4 time all the way through.

243
00:24:21,783 --> 00:24:24,534
旋律會變，但是節奏一直不變
The melody changes,abcbut the rhythm is constant.

244
00:24:24,954 --> 00:24:26,412
所以你就可以跟著它跳舞
So you can dance to it.

245
00:24:26,997 --> 00:24:30,947
而四重奏，是旋律和節奏都會改變。
The quartet changesboth melodically and rhythmically.

246
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:33,701
我會再放一遍。聽著。
I'm going to play them again.Listen for this.

247
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:42,711
曼菲爾德先生
Mr. Manfield.

248
00:24:49,772 --> 00:24:51,599
我們得給你找個樂器
We'll have to find an instrument for you.

249
00:24:51,775 --> 00:24:52,806
樂器？
An instrument?

250
00:24:53,527 --> 00:24:56,978
選音樂課的都要在樂團演奏。
Everybody who takes music is required to play in the orchestra.

251
00:24:58,657 --> 00:25:00,945
你會什麼樂器嗎？
Do you play something?

252
00:25:01,035 --> 00:25:02,197
鋼琴。
Piano.

253
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,495
彈一段。
Play something.

254
00:26:33,261 --> 00:26:36,546
好的，你沒必要去樂團演奏了。
Well, there's one thing you don't have to do, and that's play in the orchestra.

255
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:40,093
我想聽聽你在我家的斯坦威鋼琴上彈的怎麼樣。
I'd like to hear how you sound on the Steinway I have at home.

256
00:26:42,271 --> 00:26:43,848
出去吧
Get out of here.

257
00:26:55,536 --> 00:26:58,572
- 找到工作了，爸爸？
- 找到了，就在城裡。
- Get a job, Dad?
- You betcha I did. Right in town.

258
00:26:58,664 --> 00:27:01,499
- 我是廚師。猜是做什麼菜？
- 意大利菜？
- I'm a cook. Guess which kind?
- Italian?

259
00:27:01,584 --> 00:27:03,790
- 猜對啦。
- 太棒了！
- You got it.
- Radical!

260
00:27:03,878 --> 00:27:05,787
非得這麼說話麼
Do you have to say that?

261
00:27:08,383 --> 00:27:11,052
- 從哪拿到這個的？
- 公共圖書館的失物招領處。
- Where'd you get this?
- Public library lost and found.

262
00:27:11,136 --> 00:27:12,760
就在餐廳的轉角處
It's right around the corner from the restaurant.

263
00:27:12,846 --> 00:27:16,179
這四月會很冷，我覺得你用得到
April can be cold up here.I thought you might needthese.

264
00:27:16,475 --> 00:27:18,847
別讓你這雙拿球棒的手凍裂了。
Keep those slugger hands from cracking.

265
00:27:18,936 --> 00:27:20,596
- 進球隊了麼？
- 嗯
- Did you make the team?
- Yeah.

266
00:27:20,688 --> 00:27:22,846
- 太棒了
- 我有什麼？
- Great.
- What about me?

267
00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:26,559
對不起，孩子。東西都沒有你的號。週末我去電影院試試
Sorry, kid. Nothing in your size. Have to try a movie theater on the weekend.

268
00:27:26,653 --> 00:27:29,144
這提醒了我，週六得去砍些柴火
Which reminds me, we have to chop some firewood on Saturday.

269
00:27:29,239 --> 00:27:31,196
哦，爸爸，我明天做這個。明天我不上學。
Oh, Dad, I'll do it tomorrow.I'm not going to school.

270
00:27:31,408 --> 00:27:33,400
- 為什麼？
- 他們在拍班級合照
- How come?
- They're taking class pictures.

271
00:27:33,536 --> 00:27:34,567
好。
Right.

272
00:27:35,621 --> 00:27:38,372
- 那學校怎麼樣？
- 還不錯
- How is that school?
- Not bad.

273
00:27:39,042 --> 00:27:42,458
- 老師知道點你不知道的東西？
- 嗯，他們還不錯。
- Teachers know anything you don't?
- Yeah, they're okay.

274
00:27:42,546 --> 00:27:44,289
你註冊的時候遇到麻煩了嗎？
Did you have any trouble with the registration?

275
00:27:44,381 --> 00:27:46,504
今天放學的時候我去見了輔導員。
I had to see the guidance counselor at the end of the day.

276
00:27:46,675 --> 00:27:47,754
然後呢？
And?

277
00:27:47,843 --> 00:27:50,879
他想知道我要申請哪個大學
He wanted to know what colleges I was applying to.

278
00:27:51,597 --> 00:27:53,091
你告訴他什麼了？
What did you tell him?

279
00:27:53,182 --> 00:27:55,174
呃，我說我還沒決定。
Well, I said I hadn't decided yet.

280
00:27:55,768 --> 00:27:58,056
好。就和他們隨便說點什麼，然後忘了吧。
Good. Just tell them something, and forget about it.

281
00:27:58,146 --> 00:28:00,185
不然他們會一直偷聽你。
Otherwise they'll keep bugging you.

282
00:28:00,273 --> 00:28:03,606
- 你怎麼樣，小東西？
- 我不要胡椒
- How about you, small stuff?
- I don't want peppers.

283
00:28:12,161 --> 00:28:13,192
上帝保佑
Bless you.

284
00:28:16,625 --> 00:28:19,412
我們班有個人真的很瘋狂
There's a kid in my class who's really crazy.

285
00:28:19,878 --> 00:28:22,499
你的精神又沒正常到哪去
You're not exactly the poster child for mental health.

286
00:28:22,589 --> 00:28:25,162
他記得火車時刻表
He knows train schedules.

287
00:28:25,426 --> 00:28:27,086
你從來不需要知道。你可以在手裡有一份，然後就都知道了。
You never know.It might have come in handy.

288
00:28:27,178 --> 00:28:29,751
真的，爸爸。整個國家的他都知道。
Really, Dad. All over the country.

289
00:28:30,056 --> 00:28:33,555
他知道火車什麼時候從奧馬哈到佐治亞州的亞特蘭大
He knows what time trains leave from Omaha to Atlanta, Georgia.

290
00:28:33,685 --> 00:28:34,716
像這樣的東西
Stuff like that.

291
00:28:34,811 --> 00:28:37,349
得認識認識這孩子。你拿著這別針幹什麼呢？
Get to know this kid.What are you doing with that safety pin?

292
00:28:37,439 --> 00:28:38,933
什麼別針？
What safety pin?

293
00:28:43,321 --> 00:28:45,444
- 我找到工作了。
- 真的？
- I got a job.
- Really?

294
00:28:45,948 --> 00:28:47,406
告訴我們，親愛的。
Tell us, my dear.

295
00:28:47,492 --> 00:28:50,528
你要怎麼奉獻這個虛假的資本主義經濟？
How are you going to contribute to this false, capitalist economy?

296
00:28:51,329 --> 00:28:54,828
我要做一個米爾頓·克斯維爾醫生的接待員。
I'm going to be a receptionist for a Dr. Milton Cosswell.

297
00:28:54,917 --> 00:28:55,948
- 是嗎？
- 對。
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

298
00:28:56,085 --> 00:28:58,077
郵局有個招聘的告示
There was a sign up at the post office.

299
00:28:58,170 --> 00:29:00,079
他不介意付我現金
He doesn't mind paying me in cash.

300
00:29:00,798 --> 00:29:02,422
他甚至都沒問為什麼。
He didn't even ask why.

301
00:29:02,508 --> 00:29:05,343
應該是對他避稅還是什麼的有好處吧。
It's probably good for his taxes, or something.

302
00:29:05,637 --> 00:29:08,638
不管怎麼樣，有工作意味著如果我們需要，就可以拿點東西來用
Anyway, it means I can pick up supplies, if we need them.

303
00:29:08,974 --> 00:29:12,094
他看起來是個好人
He seems like a pretty nice guy.

304
00:29:16,691 --> 00:29:18,351
謝謝媽媽
Mom, thanks.

305
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:23,109
聽著不錯。看起來我們都得到想要的東西了
Sounds good. Looks like we all got what we wanted.

306
00:30:52,004 --> 00:30:53,664
有人在家嗎？
Hello, is anyone home?

307
00:31:06,519 --> 00:31:07,550
有人嗎？
Hello?

308
00:33:07,527 --> 00:33:09,021
你是誰？
Who are you?

309
00:33:09,279 --> 00:33:11,022
我是住這的。那你是誰？
I live here. Who are you?

310
00:33:12,449 --> 00:33:14,940
- 菲利普斯先生是你父親？
- 是。
- Is Mr. Phillips your father?
- Yes.

311
00:33:15,703 --> 00:33:17,161
穿粉色衣服的這是你……
And is this you in the pink-

312
00:33:17,246 --> 00:33:18,491
哦，別想它了。
I've destroyed the negative.

313
00:33:18,581 --> 00:33:21,368
現在你知道我是這的人了，該說說你了
So now we've determined that I belong here. Let's talk about you.

314
00:33:21,793 --> 00:33:25,292
你父親說我可以彈他的鋼琴，而且門是開著的
Your father said I could use the piano. And the door was open.

315
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:27,871
- 我們有門鈴的
- 我按門鈴了
- We do have a bell.
- I rang the bell.

316
00:33:27,966 --> 00:33:30,801
沒人應，我就進來了，對不起。
No one answered, so I came in. I'm sorry.

317
00:33:31,053 --> 00:33:32,677
你在我父親的學校？
You go to the school?

318
00:33:32,930 --> 00:33:34,009
是
Yeah.

319
00:33:34,098 --> 00:33:37,348
- 我沒見過你。
- 那是因為我剛來
- I haven't seen you there.
- That's because I just started.

320
00:33:37,435 --> 00:33:39,059
所以你今天怎麼沒去上學？
So how come you're not there?

321
00:33:40,105 --> 00:33:42,774
我昨晚發燒了，我媽讓我呆在家裡
I had a fever last night.My mom made me stay home.

322
00:33:42,858 --> 00:33:46,441
- 那你為什麼不呆在家裡？
- 我今天好多了，還很無聊
- Why didn't you?
- I felt better today. And I was bored.

323
00:33:47,321 --> 00:33:49,563
你真奇怪。我今天翹課了。
You're strange. I cut.

324
00:33:49,699 --> 00:33:52,700
我可不想和這些非人類一塊拍照。
I didn't feel like having my picture taken with those subhumans.

325
00:33:53,203 --> 00:33:54,780
你很好，你知道
You're very good, you know.

326
00:33:54,913 --> 00:33:56,573
我還可以
I'm okay.

327
00:33:57,290 --> 00:33:58,784
你叫什麼？
What's your name?

328
00:33:59,167 --> 00:34:01,325
- 麥克。
- 我叫羅娜
- Michael.
- I'm Lorna.

329
00:34:02,171 --> 00:34:03,333
我還是走吧
I'd better be going.

330
00:34:03,422 --> 00:34:05,628
- 你從哪來？
- 奧克蘭。
- Where are you from?
- Oakland.

331
00:34:05,841 --> 00:34:08,510
- 你生在加州？
- 不，紐約
- You born in California?- No, New York.

332
00:34:08,720 --> 00:34:09,882
真的？
Really?

333
00:34:09,971 --> 00:34:13,304
我想去紐約上學，但我媽媽怕我被搶劫
I want to go to school in New York, but my mother's afraid I'll get mugged.

334
00:34:14,184 --> 00:34:15,844
你家經常搬？
Your family move around a lot?

335
00:34:15,978 --> 00:34:17,436
不，不是。你彈鋼琴麼？
No, not really. You play?

336
00:34:18,147 --> 00:34:20,472
天哪，不。我可受不了練琴。
God, no. I couldn't stand to practice.

337
00:34:20,691 --> 00:34:23,016
我哥哥是演奏家
My older brother is the virtuoso.

338
00:34:23,361 --> 00:34:26,860
他上耶魯，他做什麼都對。你要去哪個大學？
He's at Yale. He does everything right.Where are you going?

339
00:34:31,453 --> 00:34:34,288
哦，那個啊。我還沒怎麼想過。
Oh, that.I haven't thought about that much.

340
00:34:34,540 --> 00:34:38,372
你還沒怎麼想過？下個學期可就要申請了。
You haven't though about it much? You're going to have to apply next semester.

341
00:34:40,379 --> 00:34:41,577
是麼？
Yeah?

342
00:34:42,340 --> 00:34:44,083
你什麼意思，「是麼」？
What do you mean, "Yeah?"

343
00:34:46,553 --> 00:34:49,922
你看，我真的……真的得走了。
Look, I really... I gotta go.

344
00:34:51,391 --> 00:34:53,051
你很有資格。
You're certifiable.

345
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:55,054
不用謝。
You're welcome.

346
00:35:02,278 --> 00:35:04,436
曼菲爾德先生，我想和你說句話。
Mr. Manfield, I'd like a word with you.

347
00:35:08,076 --> 00:35:10,745
我知道你昨天去了我家。
I understand you had occasion to visit my house yesterday.

348
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:13,323
我去看你的鋼琴了
I went to look at your piano.

349
00:35:13,416 --> 00:35:15,704
我知道你不只是看看而已。
I understand you did more than look at it.

350
00:35:16,627 --> 00:35:18,952
- 你家裡有鋼琴嗎？
- 沒有，先生
- Do you have a piano at home?
- No, sir.

351
00:35:20,173 --> 00:35:21,501
那你怎麼練習？
How do you practice?

352
00:35:22,217 --> 00:35:23,545
我不能常練。
I can't much.

353
00:35:25,220 --> 00:35:27,093
你是個很有才華的音樂家，曼菲爾德……
You're a talented musician, Manfield...

354
00:35:27,181 --> 00:35:29,553
但你沒有像罪犯一樣（進別人家）的權利。
but that doesn't give you theright to act like a criminal.

355
00:35:29,642 --> 00:35:30,970
清楚了嗎？
Is that clear?

356
00:35:32,437 --> 00:35:33,551
是的，先生。
Yes, sir.

357
00:35:38,151 --> 00:35:39,182
曼菲爾德？
Manfield?

358
00:35:41,488 --> 00:35:43,148
我們會給你找個鋼琴。
We'll find you a piano.

359
00:35:50,623 --> 00:35:52,615
讓我看看，姑娘們。
Now let me see, girls.

360
00:35:56,630 --> 00:35:59,584
謝謝，去隊尾吧。
Thank you. Just go to the back of the line.

361
00:36:02,136 --> 00:36:04,424
你很有資格啊。
You are certifiable.

362
00:36:05,223 --> 00:36:08,224
這是怎麼回事？開什麼玩笑？你上廚藝課？
What is this? Some sort of smart-ass joke? You're taking cooking?

363
00:36:08,309 --> 00:36:09,637
我想學做菜。
I want to learn how to cook.

364
00:36:09,727 --> 00:36:13,594
是啊，對。你有強烈的慾望想學怎麼做Apple Brown Betty（一種用蘋果和麵包屑製成的甜點）。
Yeah, right. You have a burning desire to learn how to make Apple Brown Betty.

365
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:16,857
你要是這麼想，那你在這幹什麼？
What are you doing here,if you think so highly of it?

366
00:36:16,944 --> 00:36:18,901
他們不讓我學機械……
They wouldn't let me take auto mechanics...

367
00:36:18,988 --> 00:36:21,443
我也沒時間把這事告到最高法院。
and I didn't have time to take the issue to the Supreme Court.

368
00:36:21,532 --> 00:36:25,067
既然剩下了菲利普斯和曼菲爾德
Now that leaves Phillips and Manfield.

369
00:36:25,370 --> 00:36:27,861
你們可以用最後一張台嗎？
Please, would you take the last booth?

370
00:36:30,125 --> 00:36:32,117
今天的菜譜……
Today's menu...

371
00:36:32,628 --> 00:36:35,582
是金槍魚核桃砂鍋
is tuna-walnut casserole.

372
00:36:35,673 --> 00:36:37,915
這大概也算是機械吧
This may be auto mechanics after all.

373
00:36:38,718 --> 00:36:41,125
拿著四杯量的量杯。
Take your four-cup measuring bowl.

374
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:43,925
你知道，我父親覺得你是切片麵包之外最好的東西
You know, my father thinks you're the best thing since sliced bread.

375
00:36:44,015 --> 00:36:45,924
他可不是這麼對我說的
That's not what he told me.

376
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:47,803
一罐金槍魚
A can of tuna.

377
00:36:48,186 --> 00:36:50,013
聽著，別擔心。別讓他嚇著你。
Listen, don't worry.Don't let him scare you.

378
00:36:50,105 --> 00:36:52,228
如果他覺得你可以演奏，你就可以為所欲為了。
You can do anything if he thinks you can play music.

379
00:36:53,067 --> 00:36:55,059
半杯核桃
Half a cup of walnuts.

380
00:36:55,778 --> 00:36:58,269
週六有室內樂演奏會
We're having a chamber music concert Saturday.

381
00:36:58,406 --> 00:37:00,778
無聊的要死，你還得穿的像去葬禮一樣……
And they're boring as hell, you have to dress for a funeral...

382
00:37:00,867 --> 00:37:02,361
但是你應該會喜歡。想來嗎？
but you'd probably like it.abcYou want to come?

383
00:37:02,452 --> 00:37:04,444
兩根芹菜
Two stalks of celery.

384
00:37:05,122 --> 00:37:08,289
- 好，我考慮考慮。芹菜。
- 芹菜。
- Yeah, I've got to think about it. Celery.
- Celery.

385
00:37:08,667 --> 00:37:09,698
在這。
Here.

386
00:37:11,587 --> 00:37:14,541
他被那些資產階級的垃圾引誘了
He's getting seduced by all this bourgeois crap.

387
00:37:14,632 --> 00:37:17,633
- 去他的室內樂
- 那是音樂啊，看在上帝的份上
- Fucking chamber music.
- It's music, for God's sake.

388
00:37:17,719 --> 00:37:20,720
頹廢的，白皮膚的，特權階級的垃圾
Decadent, white-skinned, privileged crap.

389
00:37:21,223 --> 00:37:24,556
一大堆人打著領帶穿著連褲襪坐著扶手椅，呆在一塊
Lot of people sitting around in ties and pantyhose in wing chairs...

390
00:37:24,643 --> 00:37:26,635
- 像在你母親家
- 像在我母親家。
- like at your mother's house.
- Like at my mother's house.

391
00:37:26,729 --> 00:37:28,057
他不能去。
He's not going.

392
00:37:28,522 --> 00:37:30,561
- 誰說的？
- 我說的！
- Says who?
- Says me!

393
00:37:30,650 --> 00:37:33,983
- 我不信。
- 看我的口型：他不能去！
- I don't believe you.
- Read my lips: He's not going.

394
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:36,478
你什麼時候成了文化部長？
Since when did you become the minister of culture?

395
00:37:36,573 --> 00:37:38,482
如果是搖滾演唱會你就讓他去了。
You'd let him go if it was a rock 'n' roll concert.

396
00:37:38,575 --> 00:37:40,733
- 對了！我會的。對。
- 難以置信。
- That's right! You bet I would. Yes.
- Unbelievable.

397
00:37:40,828 --> 00:37:42,820
你神經錯亂了嗎？
Are you out of your mind?

398
00:37:43,330 --> 00:37:46,781
我不會讓他去的，因為不安全
I'm not letting him go because it's not safe.

399
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:51,458
他又不至於暴露在整個沃特福德面前
He doesn't have to be on display for the entire community of Waterford.

400
00:37:52,924 --> 00:37:55,082
而且就因為這不是搖滾演唱會
And because it's not rock and roll.

401
00:37:56,470 --> 00:37:59,257
你以為你很可愛，爸爸，但你就是垃圾。
You think you're cute, Dad,but you're full of shit.

402
00:38:00,808 --> 00:38:02,931
- 不要對我這樣講話。
- 為什麼？
- Don't talk to me like that.
- Why?

403
00:38:03,102 --> 00:38:05,427
我們不應該質疑權威麼？你就是那麼教我的！
Aren't we supposed to question authority? You taught me that!

404
00:38:05,563 --> 00:38:07,602
你以為你是誰？巴頓將軍？
Who do you think you are? General Patton?

405
00:38:07,690 --> 00:38:10,975
為什麼上學對我來說還比去音樂會危險了？
Why is it any more dangerous for me to go to school than it is to go to the concert?

406
00:38:11,069 --> 00:38:14,652
因為在學校還有600個孩子
Because there are 600 other kids at the school.

407
00:38:16,909 --> 00:38:18,486
讓我歇會吧
Give me a break.

408
00:38:19,036 --> 00:38:20,494
你不可以去。
You're not going.

409
00:39:47,175 --> 00:39:49,333
曼菲爾德先生！我們有這樣的享受應該感謝什麼？
Mr. Manfield! To what do we owe this pleasure?

410
00:39:49,427 --> 00:39:51,004
羅娜邀請的我。
Lorna invited me.

411
00:39:51,179 --> 00:39:53,848
她通常沒這麼好的審美。
She usually doesn't show such good judgment.

412
00:39:54,182 --> 00:39:57,515
我很高興。我想讓你見一些人。
I'm delighted. There's some people I want you to meet.

413
00:39:57,853 --> 00:40:00,260
山姆，這是麥克·曼菲爾德，我和你說過的那個男孩
Sam, this is Michael Manfield,the boy I was telling you about.

414
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:01,387
- 很高興認識你。
- 你好
- Pleased to meet you.
- Hi.

415
00:40:01,482 --> 00:40:03,807
也許我們可以讓你給我們彈點什麼
Perhaps we can convince you to play something for us.

416
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:05,977
我什麼都沒準備
I have nothing prepared.

417
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:09,071
有一天我聽見你在彈勃拉姆斯，真是美
I heard you working on some Brahms the other day. It was perfectly lovely.

418
00:40:09,157 --> 00:40:10,948
第二次幕間休息之後你可以彈一彈
You can play it after the second intermission.

419
00:40:11,034 --> 00:40:14,782
我很樂意，但是我真的要去朋友家接我弟弟
I'd like to, but I really have to go pick up my brother at a friend's house.

420
00:40:14,872 --> 00:40:16,829
你可以在走之前彈。
You can play before you have to go.

421
00:40:16,916 --> 00:40:17,947
聽著，爸爸，抱歉
Listen, Dad, would you excuse me?

422
00:40:18,042 --> 00:40:19,240
我想帶麥克吃點東西
I'd like to get Michael something to eat.

423
00:40:19,335 --> 00:40:21,707
- 希望早點聽到你演奏
- 真是好東西。
- Hope to hear you soon.
- It was really good stuff.

424
00:40:29,388 --> 00:40:32,057
為什麼你不想為他們演奏？
How come you didn't want to play for them?

425
00:40:33,350 --> 00:40:37,182
如果是我自己，我不會考慮。但是你會喜歡的。
Personally, I wouldn't consider it,but you're supposed to love this stuff.

426
00:40:39,857 --> 00:40:43,724
沒關係，你不用解釋。莫扎特也是個瘋子。
It's all right. You don't have to explain.Mozart was crazy, too.

427
00:40:46,406 --> 00:40:48,694
- 想上去去我的房間麼？
- 好。
- Want to go up to my room?
- Okay.

428
00:40:49,576 --> 00:40:51,734
好啦。把牛奶喝完。
All right. Finish your milk.

429
00:41:12,852 --> 00:41:14,346
抱歉
Excuse me.

430
00:41:16,898 --> 00:41:18,725
吉他就是我的生命。
Guitar is my life.

431
00:41:28,077 --> 00:41:30,402
你很讓人迷惑，你知道
You're very confusing, you know.

432
00:41:31,247 --> 00:41:33,572
誰？我？為什麼？
Who, me? Why?

433
00:41:34,250 --> 00:41:35,827
因為有的時候你那麼直接……
'Cause sometimes you can be so straight...

434
00:41:35,919 --> 00:41:38,244
但有的時候，轉過身去你又是那樣的
and then other times, you turn around and you're like that.

435
00:41:44,136 --> 00:41:47,172
- 總是說著「是，先生」或者「不是，先生」
- 我很禮貌的
-It's always, "Yes, sir" and "No, sir. "
- I'm polite.

436
00:41:47,432 --> 00:41:49,638
- 禮貌很假。
- 不是假。
- Polite is phony.
- It's not phony.

437
00:41:51,561 --> 00:41:54,681
- 可以避免衝突。
- 你現在就在做這個麼？
- It avoids confrontation.
- Is that what you're doing now?

438
00:41:54,773 --> 00:41:56,765
你在避免衝突？
You're avoiding confrontation?

439
00:41:56,984 --> 00:41:59,107
你就沒有想說「去他媽的」的時候？
Don't you ever want to say, "Cut the shit"?

440
00:41:59,236 --> 00:42:02,153
羅娜！麥克和你在一起嗎？我想讓他出來演奏。
Lorna! Is Michael in there with you? I want him to play.

441
00:42:04,826 --> 00:42:07,613
他走了。他去接他弟弟了
He left. He went to pick up his brother.

442
00:42:08,121 --> 00:42:10,160
我以為這是我的房間
I thought this was my room.

443
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:14,242
你媽媽讓你下樓
Your mother wants you downstairs.

444
00:42:26,099 --> 00:42:27,379
那有棵樹（可以從那出去）。
There's a tree.

445
00:43:16,780 --> 00:43:19,271
鮑威爾太太？可以見醫生了。
Mrs. Powell? The doctor will see you now.

446
00:43:24,121 --> 00:43:26,446
我把錢包落在這了嗎？
Did I leave my purse out here?

447
00:43:28,835 --> 00:43:29,866
謝謝。
Thank you.

448
00:43:33,131 --> 00:43:34,459
你好？
Excuse me?

449
00:43:35,133 --> 00:43:36,164
你好！
Excuse me!

450
00:43:37,219 --> 00:43:38,843
你有預約嗎？
Do you have an appointment?

451
00:43:41,140 --> 00:43:42,385
沒有。
Nope.

452
00:43:55,155 --> 00:43:56,483
格斯。
Gus!

453
00:43:58,826 --> 00:44:00,783
吃什麼，媽媽？
What's cooking, mama?

454
00:44:02,413 --> 00:44:05,829
我看著你，我就能看到你站在密歇根街角……
I look at you, and I can see you standing on the corner of Michigan Avenue...

455
00:44:06,626 --> 00:44:09,746
穿著墨西哥式上衣，戴著那瘋癲的銀色東西
in a Mexican blouse and those crazy silver things.

456
00:44:09,963 --> 00:44:11,754
大銀耳環
Big silver earrings.

457
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:14,792
天哪，那是好久以前了
God, that was a long time ago.

458
00:44:16,262 --> 00:44:17,590
阿瑟怎麼樣？
How's Artie?

459
00:44:18,473 --> 00:44:19,801
他挺好。
He's okay.

460
00:44:20,642 --> 00:44:22,634
其實他好極了
He's great, actually.

461
00:44:23,645 --> 00:44:26,978
他在佛羅里達的一處有毒垃圾堆放點做了點工作
He did some work in Florida on a toxic waste dump.

462
00:44:27,441 --> 00:44:30,192
在這，他組織了個個食品公司
Here, he organized a food co-op...

463
00:44:30,277 --> 00:44:32,150
他還在讓他的餐廳集團化
and he's trying to get his restaurant to unionize.

464
00:44:32,238 --> 00:44:34,396
你和阿瑟怎麼樣
And how's you and Artie?

465
00:44:35,157 --> 00:44:36,485
我們還好
We're okay.

466
00:44:37,410 --> 00:44:41,158
我是說，你知道，很艱難
I mean, you know, it's hard.

467
00:44:41,248 --> 00:44:42,742
我想你。
I think about you.

468
00:44:44,668 --> 00:44:46,162
我想你
I think about you.

469
00:44:48,756 --> 00:44:50,333
希望你是安全的
I hope you're safe.

470
00:44:52,635 --> 00:44:54,462
你怎麼做到的？
How do you manage this?

471
00:44:54,762 --> 00:44:56,090
有房子
Got a house...

472
00:44:56,598 --> 00:44:57,926
兩個孩子
two kids.

473
00:44:58,934 --> 00:45:01,472
就像你過著正常人的生活
It's kind of like you're leading a regular life.

474
00:45:02,396 --> 00:45:03,890
我很會撒謊
I'm a good liar.

475
00:45:05,399 --> 00:45:07,023
但是我累了
But I'm tired.

476
00:45:10,113 --> 00:45:11,607
媽的
Shit.

477
00:45:18,747 --> 00:45:19,778
